  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0d82\u0da0\u0db1 \u0d85\u0db7\u0dd2\u0dba\u0ddd\u0d9c\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dc5\u0dcf \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd1 - \u0daf\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd6\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db1\u0db8\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Minister Kanchana will not run away from the challenge - he is ready to leave",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Power and Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekera says that he accepted the Ministry of Power and Energy knowing that he would have to be scolded and he will not run away from the challenge.",
        "In a press conference held in Colombo today, he stated that if anyone else takes up the challenge of supplying fuel, he is ready to support it.",
        "He said that he would apologize to the people for the existing situation and would work to end the fuel queues in a systematic way in the future."
      ],
